An Act to prevent nonprofit institutions from avoiding wetlands or natural resource protections
under the so-called Dover Amendment.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. The General Court hereby finds and declares that the use of the so-called
2 Dover amendment by nonprofit institutions to avoid wetland or natural resource area protections
3 may be harmful to the public health and environment.
4 SECTION 2. Section 3 of chapter 40A of the General Laws, as appearing in the 2020
5 Official Edition, is hereby amended by striking out, in line 53, the words “restrict the” and
6 inserting in place thereof the following words:- restrict, other than through wetlands or natural
7 resource area protections.
